settle for bacon and eggs this morning. Sit.

11:25.351 --> 11:27.819
<i>So then I'm supposed to go
Just because you want me to?</i>

11:27.887 --> 11:30.185
<i>Because I know
what's right for you.</i>

11:30.256 --> 11:34.249
You don't even know who I am.
I mean, college isn't right for everyone.

11:34.326 --> 11:37.090
Seventeen years old
and he thinks he knows everything.

11:37.163 --> 11:40.257
Oh, okay. The older you
are, the smarter you are?

11:40.332 --> 11:44.632
<i>Fine. We'll ask Pop. He's older than
both of us, all of us, put together.</i>

11:44.704 --> 11:46.968
<i>Oh, no. Don't put your
grandfather in the middle of this.</i>

11:47.039 --> 11:49.371
Why? Don't you respect
your own father's wisdom?

11:49.442 --> 11:51.376
You're my son, not his.

11:51.444 --> 11:55.778
Pop, you were a teenager
when you left Ireland, right?

11:55.848 --> 12:00.410
<i>He was trying to escape a potato famine,
not run away to Greenwich Village.</i>

12:00.486 --> 12:03.785
He wanted a better life,
which is exactly what I want.

12:03.856 --> 12:05.983
<i>I want to be a musician.</i>

12:06.058 --> 12:08.117
Or a long-haired hippie bum.

12:08.194 --> 12:11.288
<i>Dad, I have the talent.
I gotta at least try.</i>

12:11.363 --> 12:14.730
You can either go to City College
or come to work with me.

12:14.800 --> 12:16.927
<i>You know, uh, maybe-</i>

12:17.002 --> 12:20.460
- maybe there's a way you could do both.
- You stay out of this, Pop.

12:20.539 --> 12:23.770
<i>Wh-Why should he? He's been more of
a father to me than you ever have.</i>

12:48.100 --> 12:50.466
<i>Look, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, uh, Son.</i>

12:50.536 --> 12:54.404
Uh, he's young, you know?
Don't make excuses.

12:54.473 --> 12:56.964
I'm not. I'm on your side
on this one. That's a first.

12:57.042 --> 13:00.205
Look, could you just slow down
for a second? I'm sorry, Dad.

13:00.279 --> 13:02.213
How's your hip doing?

13:02.281 --> 13:05.580
It's good. It's good. It's, uh- It's
feelin' good. L- I feel like I'm 40 today.

13:05.651 --> 13:07.915
Good. That's good, Sam. Great,
Dad. I'll see you tonight.

13:07.987 --> 13:10.615
<i>- And you're sounding like your sane.
- I am sane.</i>

13:10.689 --> 13:15.456
Dad, I never said you were insane.

13:15.528 --> 13:18.656
All right. Maybe that's, um-
that's too strong of a word.

13:18.731 --> 13:22.667
But you think that
I'm losing touch, right?

13:22.735 --> 13:28.435
Look, I-I know it can't be easy
living with someone... eccentric like me.

13:28.507 --> 13:32.170
